DELETE - Static variable in interface model.Actions
Static integer that is used for informing Observers of Delete action that happened to the model so it can be properly handled.
delete(DeleteType, ArrayList<MutableTreeNode>) - Method in interface model.Actions
This method is Overrideable latter on by the class which implements Actions interface or be left default which is empty.
General purpose of method is to delete the node which implements this interface with different type of deletion.

DeleteType - Enum in model
This ENUM represents different deletion types
COMPLETE_DELETE = represents delete of all references if node is shared DELETE_JUST_SELECTED = represents delete of just selected node no matter if it is shared UNBIND = when you want to delete the node, but not completely just save it to draft
